org.eclipse.scada.vi.details.model

Interface ReadableComponent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Component
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ProgressComponent, TextComponent, TextInputComponent, TextInputMultiComponent, ValueComponent, ValueSetComponent, WriteableComponent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProgressComponentImpl, ReadableComponentImpl, TextComponentImpl, TextInputComponentImpl, TextInputMultiComponentImpl, ValueComponentImpl, ValueSetComponentImpl, WriteableComponentImpl

    public interface ReadableComponent
extends Component
    A representation of the model object 'Readable Component'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Format
    • Decimal
    • Attribute
    • Hd Connection Id
    • Hd Item Id
    • Hd Query String
    • Is Text

    See Also:
    DetailViewPackage.getReadableComponent()

      • getHdQueryString

        java.lang.String getHdQueryString()
        Returns the value of the 'Hd Query String' attribute.

        If the meaning of the 'Hd Query String' attribute isn't clear, there really should be more of a description here...

        The query string in the format: START:END[:MIN:MAX]. Where START, END is the relative start and end time in milliseconds based on now. And MIN, MAX is the range for the Y-axis.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Hd Query String' attribute.
        See Also:
        setHdQueryString(String), DetailViewPackage.getReadableComponent_HdQueryString()
